caption: I don’t waste my time waiting in a drive-through that I can’t get out of.  You have now officially wasted three hours of my week playing around with Taco Bell driving back-and-forth to different stores not to mention very very poor and rude management. I really hope somebody can read this and make amends and fix this location before it is no longer a location at all. Happy New Year’s and I would love to see a better Taco Bell one of these years. I have lived in this area now for 24 years since I have grown up in this part of town. That has been the worst restaurant in the business by far and I work all over to Maryland and back all the way down to North Carolina and South Carolina and it is the most rudest has visited the Taco Bell off the 1000 block of West Broad Street on about four cases in the past week. The manager stated to me she has no time to argue with me even though I wasn’t arguing. She is very rude. She would not give me her name. As a business owner myself this is unacceptable and I would like to know how many other managers in the Taco Bell corporation cannot purchase inventory. Not only has she told me now four different times in about two weeks maybe more that she cannot get nacho cheese fries because she is out but she has another store bringing them to her. That is a obvious. Why? Because it has going on now for at least three times in the past week at minimum.  This her duty to make sure her inventory is properly adjusted to the sales. If she can’t do simple math she should not be a manager. I don’t have a name. She would not give it but the bottom line is it is really bothersome. Update. Once I arrive to the other Taco Bell that’s approximately 3 miles down the road in Centerville. They did have the cheese fries, not only that, they had sealed containers, everything was handed out properly like it should be during a Covid pandemic and numbers are climbing without proper vaccinations being given out!? I would love to know if anybody else has had these experiences with their locations. This is probably one of the worst Taco Bells I have ever been through. I could go on with mouse and mouse of complaints but there’s no need.  Clearly they don’t want to sell cheese fries. I don’t understand. That’s probably one of the easiest things to sell. That’s the only thing I even purchase at Taco Bell due to all of the other issues I’ve had in the past. I really hope things get better and I just want to make sure the upper management knows. Nobody wants to wait in line and then get Boston for up to 20 minutes because they don’t have product that they say they carry. If you don’t have it make sure you have a sign at least stating so so that I don’t waste my time waiting in a drive-through that I can’t get out of.  You have now officially wasted three hours of my week playing around with Taco Bell driving back-and-forth to different stores not to mention very very poor and rude management. I really hope somebody can read this and make amends and fix this location before it is no longer a location at all.  I will make sure to file a formal complaint when I have a moment. I’m not wasting anymore time with Taco Bell at the moment. I won’t be visiting that location anymore and I will follow up with further reviews on other websites as well like Yelp and also Google. I really hope something changes because if it doesn’t they will be shutting the doors there soon. I can promise you that.

Taco Bell stores are awesome in general. But, the one in Circle Center suffers from price bloat because they know that they are dealing with a captive audience that must pay the prices that they want or they don't get anything. The quality is the same as other Taco Bell stores. But the price for some items is as much as double what stand alone stores would be capable of charging.
